Task 1: Automated Backup System
Create src/lib/backup-manager.js. createBackup(): tar.gz /data/.openclaw + /data/workspace into
/data/backups/backup-{ISO}.tar.gz. Embed SHA-256 manifest. Keep last 10 local (delete oldest).
restoreBackup(name): extract, verify manifest integrity before overwriting. scheduleBackups(): setInterval per
BACKUP_INTERVAL_MINUTES env (default 60). Wire graceful shutdown hook: import in server.js SIGTERM handler,
call createBackup() before gateway shutdown. S3/R2: if BACKUP_S3_BUCKET + BACKUP_S3_KEY +
BACKUP_S3_SECRET set, pnpm add @aws-sdk/client-s3, upload after local backup. Keep 30 remote. API routes in
server.js: GET /setup/api/backups (list), POST /setup/api/backups (trigger manual), GET /setup/api/backups/:name
(download), POST /setup/api/backups/:name/restore. Write tests: test/lib/backup-manager.test.js (create, restore,
rotation, manifest verification).
AC: Backup on schedule + SIGTERM. Local retention 10. Corrupted archive rejected.
